<figureCitation box="[251,317,1997,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,253,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,251,1807]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Odontothrips iranensis sp. n.: (1) head; (2) antenna; (3) antennal segments VI – VIII; (4) abdominal tergite IX (male); (5) fore leg, apex of tibia to tarsus; (6) fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222298/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="599">
Fig. 
<number box="[301,317,1997,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="599" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); sternites without discal setae and any pore plates. Genitalia bearing one pair of endothecal stout spines.
</paragraph>
